<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781538770221" class="external" target="_blank"><i>A More Perfect Party: The Night Shirley Chisholm and Diahann Carroll Reshaped Politics</i></a> by Juanita Tolliver</strong></p>
<p>One night in 1972 in Beverly Hills the political and Hollywood A-list gathered at actress Diahann Carrol’s house to celebrate Shirley Chisholm’s presidential candidacy. Juanita Tolliver deconstructs this iconic event, capturing the power and lasting significance of the evening and Chisholm’s presidential run.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="268258" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/for-womens-history-month-a-reproductive-rights-reading-list/abortion-7/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion.jpg" data-orig-size="810,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="abortion" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-203x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-691x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-268258" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-203x300.jpg" alt="" width="203" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-203x300.jpg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-691x1024.jpg 691w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-768x1138.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/abortion.jpg 810w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 203px) 100vw, 203px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593800232" class="external" target="_blank"><i>Abortion Our Bodies, Their Lies, and the Truths We Use to Win</i></a> by Jessica Valenti</strong></p>
<p>Famous in feminist circles for her <em>Abortion Every Day</em> Substack, which forensically chronicles how reproductive rights are being curtailed law-by-law, state-by-state, Valenti lays out the political and legal landscape of post-<i>Roe </i>America in this short, succinct book.</p>
